condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :FA - Section IV B | Description :Notwithstanding the provisions of Part A of this Section, withdrawal shall onlybe made for payments made under Category (1) once the Association has received satisfactory evidence, that Assam has duly made allResettlement Payments due under the Original Projectin accordance with the provisions of the relevant social mitigation and/orresettlement plan prepared under the R&R Policy. | Due Date :15-Mar-2012

Finance Agreement :PA - Schedule 2 - 1 | Description :Assam shall implement the Project in accordance with the provisions of theOperational Manual and the Financial Management Manual in a manner satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date :20-Sep-2009

Finance Agreement :PA - Schedule 2 - 10 | Description :Assam & the Association shall review performance of the Investment GrantScheme, & shall make adjustments as appropriate to the design of the investment Grant Scheme | Due Date :31-Mar-2006

Finance Agreement :PA - Schedule 2 - 12 | Description :Assam shall carry out an independent audit of the implementation of theEnvironmental Management Framework & Resettlement & Rehabilitation Policy under the Project every 2 years of with the report | DueDate :20-Sep-2009

Finance Agreement :PA - Schedule 2 - 13 | Description :30 days after the Effective date, a qualified firm for the purpose ofcarrying out monitoring & evaluation of the Project under TORsatisfactory to the Association | Due Date :24-Mar-2005
Finance Agreement :PA - Schedule 2 - 3 | Description :Assam shall maintain the PCU with powers, functions, composition, resources,and staff, satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date :20-Sep-2009

Finance Agreement :PA - Schedule 2 - 6 | Description :Assam shall provide adequate finding in accordance with its budgetaryprocedures & implement annual Maintenance Plans on core ruralroads in the Project districts in a manner satisfactory to the Assoc |Due Date :20-Sep-2009
